1
00:00:40,684 --> 00:00:45,895
<i>(narrator) The Pilgrim's Progress.
From this World to That Which is to Come,</i>

2
00:00:46,765 --> 00:00:49,655
<i>Delivered Under the Similitude of a Dream.</i>

3
00:00:52,084 --> 00:00:55,850
<i>Wherein is Discovered,
The Manner of His Setting Out,</i>

4
00:00:56,365 --> 00:00:58,129
<i>His Dangerous Journey</i>

5
00:00:59,005 --> 00:01:02,009
<i>And Safe Arrival at the Desired Country.</i>

6
00:01:02,925 --> 00:01:05,007
(slow string music)

7
00:01:23,886 --> 00:01:26,014
(wind blowing)

8
00:01:44,727 --> 00:01:46,809
(string music intensifies)

9
00:01:52,247 --> 00:01:55,854
<i>(narrator) As I walked through
the wilderness of this world,</i>

10
00:01:55,967 --> 00:01:59,414
<i>I lighted on a certain place
where was a den</i>

11
00:02:00,607 --> 00:02:03,258
<i>and I laid me down in that place to sleep.</i>

12
00:02:04,168 --> 00:02:07,650
<i>And as I slept, I dreamed a dream.</i>

13
00:02:09,527 --> 00:02:12,895
<i>I saw a man clothed with rags,</i>

14
00:02:13,047 --> 00:02:17,848
<i>standing in a certain place with
his face from his own house</i>

15
00:02:18,008 --> 00:02:22,297
<i>book in his hand,
and a great burden upon his back.</i>

16
00:02:26,088 --> 00:02:28,295
<i>(Rick) All those years...</i>

17
00:02:30,368 --> 00:02:32,416
<i>living the life of someone...</i>

18
00:02:34,129 --> 00:02:35,699
<i>I didn't even know.</i>

19
00:03:04,450 --> 00:03:09,138
<i>(Joseph) Remember the story
I used to tell you when you were a boy...</i>

20
00:03:09,969 --> 00:03:11,573
<i>about a young prince.</i>

21
00:03:13,090 --> 00:03:15,138
<i>A knight,</i>

22
00:03:16,010 --> 00:03:18,741
<i>sent by his father, the King of the East,</i>

23
00:03:21,051 --> 00:03:22,621
<i>west into Egypt...</i>

24
00:03:23,450 --> 00:03:25,532
(indistinct chatter)

25
00:03:27,011 --> 00:03:28,581
<i>to find a pearl.</i>

26
00:03:29,771 --> 00:03:31,853
(calm woodwind music)

27
00:03:34,371 --> 00:03:37,454
<i>A pearl from the depths of the sea.</i>

28
00:03:37,611 --> 00:03:39,693
(wave crashing)

29
00:03:43,851 --> 00:03:46,138
(silent)

30
00:03:47,931 --> 00:03:50,013
<i>But when the prince arrived,</i>

31
00:03:52,691 --> 00:03:56,537
<i>the people poured him a cup
that took away his memory.</i>

32
00:03:59,372 --> 00:04:01,659
<i>He forgot he was the son of the king.</i>

33
00:04:08,172 --> 00:04:09,901
<i>Forgot about the pearl...</i>

34
00:04:16,533 --> 00:04:18,854
<i>and fell into a deep sleep.</i>

35
00:04:25,693 --> 00:04:27,980
(traffic noises fading in)

36
00:04:31,413 --> 00:04:33,541
(emergency sirens)

37
00:04:34,653 --> 00:04:36,735
(woodwind music continues)

38
00:04:39,373 --> 00:04:42,217
<i>(Joseph) The king didn't forget his son.</i>

39
00:04:44,414 --> 00:04:46,815
<i>He continued to send word...</i>

40
00:04:51,334 --> 00:04:52,859
<i>messengers...</i>

41
00:04:58,294 --> 00:05:00,103
<i>guides.</i>

42
00:05:03,855 --> 00:05:07,064
<i>But the prince slept on.</i>

43
00:05:15,255 --> 00:05:17,337
(music fades out)

44
00:05:33,015 --> 00:05:35,143
(silence)

45
00:06:09,617 --> 00:06:11,699
(low rumbling)

46
00:06:22,138 --> 00:06:24,266
(loud rattling)

47
00:06:26,538 --> 00:06:28,620
(loud clattering)

48
00:06:30,817 --> 00:06:32,307
(lamp shatters)

49
00:06:34,938 --> 00:06:37,020
(more glass shattering)

50
00:06:39,258 --> 00:06:41,340
(loud clattering)

51
00:06:48,379 --> 00:06:50,461
(distant siren)

52
00:06:50,618 --> 00:06:52,666
(rumbling stops)

53
00:06:58,939 --> 00:07:01,067
(pot crashes)
(helicopter roars)

54
00:07:02,819 --> 00:07:04,947
(indistinct TV announcer)

55
00:07:10,260 --> 00:07:11,830
(rumbling)

56
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,025
(dog barks)

57
00:07:36,901 --> 00:07:38,983
(helicopter)

58
00:07:41,621 --> 00:07:43,703
(emergency sirens)

59
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:46,988
(low rumbling)

60
00:08:31,503 --> 00:08:33,585
(traffic noises)

61
00:08:47,023 --> 00:08:49,503
<i>(Rick) You see the palm trees?</i>

62
00:08:50,503 --> 00:08:52,870
<i>They tell you anything's possible.</i>

63
00:08:56,544 --> 00:08:58,069
<i>You can be anything...</i>

64
00:09:00,183 --> 00:09:01,708
<i>do anything...</i>

65
00:09:04,064 --> 00:09:05,589
<i>start over.</i>

66
00:09:07,744 --> 00:09:09,314
(chatter)

67
00:09:09,464 --> 00:09:11,034
<i>You know?</i>

68
00:09:13,664 --> 00:09:17,510
(Scott)
I'm asking for your permission to make this

69
00:09:17,704 --> 00:09:20,753
a dramatic scene for one second...

70
00:09:44,706 --> 00:09:46,276
<i>(Joseph) My son...</i>

71
00:09:54,506 --> 00:09:56,076
<i>you are just like I am.</i>

72
00:09:59,226 --> 00:10:01,308
(slow string music)

73
00:10:02,146 --> 00:10:03,989
<i>Can't figure your life out?</i>

74
00:10:08,347 --> 00:10:10,475
<i>Can't put the pieces together?</i>

75
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:18,868
<i>Just like me.</i>

76
00:10:26,907 --> 00:10:28,557
<i>A pilgrim on this earth.</i>

77
00:10:32,827 --> 00:10:34,397
<i>A stranger.</i>

78
00:10:38,947 --> 00:10:41,029
(string music continues)

79
00:10:57,668 --> 00:10:59,432
<i>(Joseph) Fragments...</i>

80
00:11:02,629 --> 00:11:04,199
<i>pieces...</i>

81
00:11:06,469 --> 00:11:07,994
<i>of a man.</i>

82
00:11:19,909 --> 00:11:22,196
<i>(Rick) Where did I go wrong?</i>

83
00:11:24,269 --> 00:11:26,351
(music ends)

84
00:11:32,309 --> 00:11:34,437
(Splash)

85
00:11:56,551 --> 00:11:58,633
(indistinct chatter)

86
00:12:01,551 --> 00:12:03,872
<i>(Della) What you wanna talk about?</i>

87
00:12:06,551 --> 00:12:08,792
(Rick) You have nice eyes.

88
00:12:09,271 --> 00:12:10,841
Aren't I lucky.

89
00:12:11,391 --> 00:12:13,120
Where do you live?

90
00:12:13,271 --> 00:12:14,841
Why do ya wanna know?

91
00:12:16,111 --> 00:12:17,954
I want to write you a letter.

92
00:12:22,431 --> 00:12:24,877
What are you gonna say in your letter?

93
00:12:29,752 --> 00:12:32,153
(Della) Maybe you better not say it.

94
00:12:57,673 --> 00:12:59,755
(rock music fades in)

95
00:13:09,193 --> 00:13:11,275
(music overlapped by airflow)

96
00:13:14,793 --> 00:13:18,434
<i>(Della) Let's live
like nobody is ever done it before.</i>

97
00:13:18,594 --> 00:13:20,835
(high organ music)

98
00:13:21,034 --> 00:13:22,081
<i>(Della) Wicked.</i>

99
00:13:22,234 --> 00:13:25,477
<i>(narrator) Once the soul
was perfect and had wings...</i>

100
00:13:25,634 --> 00:13:26,999
(Della) Brave.

101
00:13:27,154 --> 00:13:32,524
<i>(narrator) it could soar into heaven
where only creatures with wings can be.</i>

102
00:13:32,754 --> 00:13:36,554
<i>But the soul lost its wings
and fell to Earth.</i>

103
00:13:36,714 --> 00:13:38,796
<i>There it took an earthly body.</i>

104
00:13:38,995 --> 00:13:41,839
<i>And now, while it lives in this body,</i>

105
00:13:41,995 --> 00:13:45,158
<i>no outward sign of wings can be seen.</i>

106
00:13:45,675 --> 00:13:48,485
<i>Yet the roots of its wings are still there.</i>

107
00:13:48,635 --> 00:13:52,321
<i>And the nature of wings is to try to raise
the earthbound body</i>

108
00:13:52,476 --> 00:13:54,240
<i>and soar with it into heaven.</i>

109
00:13:54,395 --> 00:13:59,401
<i>When we see a beautiful woman, or a man...</i>

110
00:13:59,995 --> 00:14:05,286
<i>the soul remembers the beauty
it used to know in heaven.</i>

111
00:14:05,915 --> 00:14:11,126
<i>And wings begin to spout,
and that makes the soul want to fly,</i>

112
00:14:11,276 --> 00:14:13,927
<i>but it cannot yet.
It is still too weak.</i>

113
00:14:14,076 --> 00:14:18,957
<i>So the man keeps staring up
into the sky like a young bird.</i>

114
00:14:19,116 --> 00:14:21,687
<i>He has lost
all interest in the world...</i>

115
00:14:22,437 --> 00:14:27,318
<i>- (Rick) Can I come over?
- (Della on phone) We just left each other.</i>

116
00:14:27,476 --> 00:14:29,160
<i>(Rick) Are you alone?</i>

117
00:14:30,917 --> 00:14:32,487
<i>(Della) Of course.</i>

118
00:14:32,637 --> 00:14:38,201
(agent 1) On my phone sheet, I got agent
writers up my ass trying to get this job.

119
00:14:38,357 --> 00:14:42,567
<i>(Rick)
I just want to sit next to you.</i>

120
00:14:43,677 --> 00:14:46,840
(agent 2) Teddy thinks
you're the guy for this.

121
00:14:48,157 --> 00:14:51,240
That means the assignment
you didn't turn in, right,

122
00:14:51,397 --> 00:14:54,765
you don't have to worry about it.
Here's what happens. That goes away.

123
00:14:55,758 --> 00:14:59,763
<i>- (Rick) What are you wearing?
- (Della on phone) A dress.</i>

124
00:14:59,918 --> 00:15:02,683
<i>- What's it made of?
- How should I know?</i>

125
00:15:03,878 --> 00:15:05,448
<i>Cotton, I guess.</i>

126
00:15:05,598 --> 00:15:08,488
We said there's no way you're gonna do it.

127
00:15:08,638 --> 00:15:12,245
So what'd we do? Said, double your quote.
And he did it.

128
00:15:12,718 --> 00:15:16,404
And that, Chuck signed off of that.
Teddy gets who he wants.

129
00:15:16,559 --> 00:15:18,641
The biggest comedy star wants you.

130
00:15:18,798 --> 00:15:23,247
Five years ago you came to me and
wanted to write big movies in Hollywood.

131
00:15:24,319 --> 00:15:27,687
- I mean...
- Okay, I don't want to see.

132
00:15:27,879 --> 00:15:32,043
(agent 1) Moments like this
don't come along, okay? This is it.

133
00:15:41,199 --> 00:15:43,281
<i>(Della) I see how you look at me.</i>

134
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:51,086
<i>You think I could make you crazy?</i>

135
00:15:55,039 --> 00:15:57,167
<i>Crack you out of your shell?</i>

136
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:07,450
<i>Make you suffer?</i>

137
00:16:30,442 --> 00:16:36,688
I think you're weak.

138
00:16:48,162 --> 00:16:49,687
<i>You don't want love.</i>

139
00:16:55,762 --> 00:16:58,413
<i>You want a love experience.</i>

140
00:16:58,562 --> 00:17:00,690
(60s pop music)

141
00:17:05,843 --> 00:17:07,925
(fades out)

142
00:17:12,163 --> 00:17:13,733
(he laughs)

143
00:17:15,763 --> 00:17:17,765
Am I bringing you back to life?

144
00:17:28,764 --> 00:17:30,289
<i>(Della) Lave and do what you like.</i>

145
00:17:34,124 --> 00:17:35,649
<i>A saint said that.</i>

146
00:17:42,284 --> 00:17:44,286
<i>(Rick) Desire so deep.</i>

147
00:17:46,604 --> 00:17:48,174
<i>I'll throw my life away.</i>

148
00:17:50,685 --> 00:17:53,052
<i>(Della) Don't go back to being dead.</i>

149
00:17:53,884 --> 00:17:55,966
(somber, distorted music)

150
00:18:03,925 --> 00:18:05,609
<i>(Della) What do you want?</i>

151
00:18:33,326 --> 00:18:36,614
We're not leading the lives
that we are meant for.

152
00:18:40,727 --> 00:18:43,253
We're meant for something else.

153
00:18:51,967 --> 00:18:54,049
(slow string music)

154
00:18:57,847 --> 00:18:59,929
(helicopter noise)

155
00:19:35,729 --> 00:19:38,699
(woman quietly) My brother will translate.

156
00:19:39,409 --> 00:19:40,979
(foreign language)

157
00:19:45,409 --> 00:19:46,979
(woman 1 speaks foreign language)

158
00:19:52,170 --> 00:19:53,934
(foreign language)

159
00:19:55,609 --> 00:19:57,737
(interpreter) He looks around.

160
00:20:00,610 --> 00:20:03,341
(foreign language)

161
00:20:05,130 --> 00:20:07,895
(interpreter)
He walks near the edge of the cliff.

162
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:11,213
(woman 2 speaks foreign language)

163
00:20:14,530 --> 00:20:16,100
(foreign language)

164
00:20:22,851 --> 00:20:26,173
(woman 1 speaks foreign language)

165
00:20:26,331 --> 00:20:28,413
(woodwind music)

166
00:20:28,570 --> 00:20:31,221
(interpreter) She says, like shadows.

167
00:20:42,891 --> 00:20:45,292
<i>(Rick) Where will I meet you?</i>

168
00:21:01,092 --> 00:21:03,174
<i>Which way should I go?</i>

169
00:21:07,293 --> 00:21:09,375
(blond woman hums)

170
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:16,335
<i>Suppose it isn't there for me,</i>

171
00:21:18,213 --> 00:21:19,783
<i>in the end?</i>

172
00:21:19,933 --> 00:21:22,140
(rushing sound)

173
00:21:45,574 --> 00:21:47,144
<i>How do I begin?</i>

174
00:22:29,135 --> 00:22:31,217
(traffic noises)

175
00:22:41,216 --> 00:22:43,059
<i>Remember how you showed up?</i>

176
00:22:44,496 --> 00:22:47,739
<i>Your wrists were taped up
like a tennis player's.</i>

177
00:22:49,976 --> 00:22:53,025
<i>You walked around
like nothing had happened.</i>

178
00:22:57,857 --> 00:23:01,782
<i>You were always doing it,
pretending everything was okay.</i>

179
00:23:03,577 --> 00:23:05,227
<i>But it wasn't.</i>

180
00:23:18,057 --> 00:23:20,378
- That's my brother, Rick.
- How are ya?

181
00:23:20,578 --> 00:23:23,787
(Barry) What's goin' on, now? Anything.
Same today?

182
00:23:24,697 --> 00:23:28,861
Don't know how many times
I thought I'd die right here on the street.

183
00:23:30,098 --> 00:23:34,069
I picked him up and I had him
in my car, and a cop pulled us over.

184
00:23:34,218 --> 00:23:39,622
I tell him, "I'm a Methodist minister
and I'm looking after you, alright?"

185
00:23:39,778 --> 00:23:41,348
And I got off.

186
00:23:41,498 --> 00:23:44,627
(players laughing
and chatting indistinctly)

187
00:24:11,740 --> 00:24:16,951
<i>(Rick) I dreamed that we were caught in
a huge tidal wave that engulfed the city.</i>

188
00:24:20,419 --> 00:24:23,662
<i>Any moment I! seemed like
we might be swept under.</i>

189
00:24:27,060 --> 00:24:30,189
<i>There was a door
that I was afraid to go through.</i>

190
00:24:32,700 --> 00:24:36,466
<i>- I touched the knob...
- (Barry) If I stuck you with a fork,</i>

191
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:41,270
<i>(Barry) Just wanna feel somethin', man.</i>

192
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:45,823
<i>Wish we could do some things.</i>

193
00:24:47,621 --> 00:24:51,182
<i>Like gain' out on the Snake River together.
Remember?</i>

194
00:24:53,901 --> 00:24:56,063
<i>Think I'd end up here.</i>

195
00:24:59,421 --> 00:25:00,946
<i>Gracias.</i>

196
00:25:01,541 --> 00:25:04,067
(Speaks Spanish)

197
00:25:08,941 --> 00:25:11,262
It's good of you to invite me out here.

198
00:25:11,422 --> 00:25:12,992
(loud slap)

199
00:25:13,422 --> 00:25:16,187
Show me what it's like
to live a normal life.

200
00:25:16,342 --> 00:25:18,629
(loud slaps)

201
00:25:24,903 --> 00:25:26,826
(Barry) Somethin' wrong?

202
00:25:30,102 --> 00:25:31,672
(soft hit)

203
00:25:31,822 --> 00:25:33,392
(chuckles)

204
00:25:35,063 --> 00:25:36,633
What's up?

205
00:25:37,662 --> 00:25:40,905
I can tell when somethin's wrong, man.
I know you.

206
00:25:59,543 --> 00:26:02,194
(Barry) What do you wanna talk about?

207
00:26:06,784 --> 00:26:10,027
I'm the only brother you got left.
You can tell me.

208
00:26:10,904 --> 00:26:12,474
I tell you stuff.

209
00:26:13,304 --> 00:26:15,432
<i>(Rick) I loved my brother then.</i>

210
00:26:18,184 --> 00:26:19,754
<i>I hated him, too.</i>

211
00:26:22,225 --> 00:26:25,468
<i>For destroying everything
I'd been trying to do.</i>

212
00:26:26,465 --> 00:26:28,832
<i>To build us back up after Billy died.</i>

213
00:26:32,425 --> 00:26:37,716
I remember when they were putting Billy
in the ground, Dad went into hysterics.

214
00:26:39,265 --> 00:26:40,835
"My son!"

215
00:26:41,505 --> 00:26:43,075
Who fucking does that?

216
00:26:45,466 --> 00:26:47,707
<i>(Rick) They said he took his life.</i>

217
00:26:49,386 --> 00:26:50,956
<i>But they don't know.</i>

218
00:26:55,186 --> 00:26:57,427
(Barry) Oh, right now. Come on.

219
00:27:00,146 --> 00:27:01,716
I gotta feel something.

220
00:27:01,907 --> 00:27:03,477
<i>(Rick) Like a snake.</i>

221
00:27:07,426 --> 00:27:08,951
<i>Swallowed him.</i>

222
00:27:10,147 --> 00:27:11,672
Come on, feel it.

223
00:27:19,507 --> 00:27:21,191
(Rick) <i>Blind.</i>

224
00:27:25,507 --> 00:27:26,554
<i>Deaf.</i>

225
00:27:38,267 --> 00:27:39,837
<i>Grasping.</i>

226
00:27:40,628 --> 00:27:43,359
<i>(Joseph) I just wanted to twist</i> a <i>cane.</i>

227
00:27:47,508 --> 00:27:49,272
<i>Strike out, break free.</i>

228
00:27:51,308 --> 00:27:52,798
<i>Didn't have the guts.</i>

229
00:28:03,549 --> 00:28:05,472
<i>(Rick) He's just an old fool.</i>

230
00:28:09,949 --> 00:28:12,316
<i>Just let him die with his blinders an.</i>

231
00:28:12,468 --> 00:28:14,596
(indistinct chatter)

232
00:28:24,910 --> 00:28:26,992
(silent)

233
00:28:32,790 --> 00:28:34,633
<i>(Joseph) Redeem my life.</i>

234
00:28:39,030 --> 00:28:40,555
<i>Justify it.</i>

235
00:28:40,710 --> 00:28:45,921
<i>Ah, look at the fierce one.
The fierceness in his eyes. The rage!</i>

236
00:28:46,070 --> 00:28:48,357
(low) inflicted upon myself...

237
00:28:50,230 --> 00:28:51,800
<i>yam on Billy.</i>

238
00:28:51,950 --> 00:28:54,032
(harp playing)

239
00:28:55,031 --> 00:28:56,601
<i>I died.</i>

240
00:28:56,750 --> 00:28:58,400
(silent)

241
00:28:58,591 --> 00:29:00,116
<i>In a different way.</i>

242
00:29:06,831 --> 00:29:09,277
